{"type":null,"faqId":34741,"title":" My phone's WLAN connection automatically disconnects after the screen times out. What can I do?","answer":"<html>\n<head>\n<META http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n<style type=\"text/css\">.b1{white-space-collapsing:preserve;}\n.d1{margin: 1.18125in 0.7875in 1.18125in 0.7875in;}\n.s1{font-weight:bold;}\n.s2{font-family:Arial Unicode MS;font-weight:bold;}\n.p1{margin-left:1.18125in;margin-top:0.11111111in;margin-bottom:0.11111111in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.p2{margin-bottom:0.027777778in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Book Antiqua;font-size:9pt;}\n.p3{margin-left:1.4409722in;margin-top:0.027777778in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body class=\"b1\">\n<div  >\n<p  >\n<span>This problem is caused by the sleep policy. On the home screen, touch </span><span class=\"s1\">Settings</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Wi-Fi</span><span>. Touch the menu key and touch </span><span class=\"s1\">Advanced Wi-Fi</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Keep Wi-Fi on during sleep</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Always</span><span>. </span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=110590\" style=\"width:1.3645834in;height:2.4770834in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/><span> </span><img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=110591\" style=\"width:1.40625in;height:2.479861in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n<p  ></p>\n<p  >\n<img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=110592\" style=\"width:0.59375in;height:0.16666667in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n<p  >\n<span>By default, </span><span class=\"s2\">Always</span><span> is selected. If you change the sleep policy, Wi-Fi disconnects when the screen times out. The implication of each option is given as below:</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s1\">Always</span><span>: The WLAN connection is always kept. </span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s1\">Only when plugged in</span><span>: The WLAN connection is kept only when the phone is charged. WLAN disconnects in 3 minutes after the screen times out if the phone is not charged. </span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s1\">Never (increases data usage)</span><span>: WLAN disconnects in 3 minutes after the screen times out. </span>\n</p>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":244,"languageName":"mm","faqCode":"9481","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1436871808000,"seriesProductName":"H30-L02","visitedTimes":1,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"HONOR 3C LTE (H30-L02)","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}